# AI-Native SDLC is the contract

`.sdlc/sdlc.yaml` is the source of truth for how this project is built. Read it
before planning any non-trivial change.

## Always do

- Identify which `phase` your work belongs to and obey that phase's `gates`.
- Stamp every artifact you write with the `common_provenance` block (agent_id,
  model, prompt_hash, trace_id, inputs_digest, created_at).
- Before writing Next.js code, read the relevant page in
  `node_modules/next/dist/docs/` (per `AGENTS.md`).
- Cite the exact rule, gate, or doc path you followed in your final message.

## Memories the agent must reload

- `.sdlc/memories/project.md` — invariant facts about this app
- `.sdlc/memories/lessons.md` — appended by the `learn` phase
- `.sdlc/memories/glossary.md` — canonical terminology

## Slash commands map to phases

`/intent`, `/spec`, `/adr`, `/implement`, `/verify`, `/review`, `/release`,
`/incident`, `/learn` — see `.cursor/commands/`.

## When in doubt

Pause and ask the maintainer rather than violate a gate or ship without
provenance. The DSL invariants are non-negotiable.
